<H2> SLES Manual Pages
[<A HREF="../manual.html#Node46"> Chapter 4 of Users Manual</A>]
</H2>

To solve linear systems, users should employ the
Scalable Linear Equations Solvers (SLES)
component, which provides an easy-to-use interface to the combination of
a Krylov subspace iterative method and a preconditioner (in the
<A HREF="KSP.html">KSP</A> and 
<A HREF="PC.html">PC</A> 
components, respectively).  SLES users can set various Krylov
subspace and preconditioning options at runtime via the options database (e.g., 
<font face ="Courier">
-pc_type jacobi -ksp_type gmres
</font face>
).  
SLES users can also set KSP and PC options directly in application
codes by first extracting the KSP and/or PC context from the SLES context via
<A HREF="SLES/SLESGetKSP.html">SLESGetKSP()</A>/
<A HREF="SLES/SLESGetPC.html">SLESGetPC()</A>
and then directly calling the KSP and PC routines listed below (e.g., 
<A HREF="KSP/KSPSetType.html">KSPSetType()</A>/
<A HREF="PC/PCSetType.html">PCSetType()</A>
).
Both KSP and PC components can be used directly to create and
destroy solvers; this approach is not needed for most users but
rather is intended for library developers.

